  "author_association": "NONE",
  "body": "What can be the causes of Envoy reseting a request in HTTP/2 connection? We have 2 levels of Envoy, L1 serves end user at the edge using HTTP/1.1 connections; L2 is the sidecar of actual service. L1 to L2 is connected via HTTP/2. We found that L2 recently has some `http2_tx_reset` which caused 503 in L1 responses. For these problematic responses, we do not see spans from L2, only see spans from L1 with response_flag `UR,URX`. All retries fail in this case no matter what number we set it to. The current retry policy is: \r\n```\r\nretry_on: connect-failure,gateway-error\r\nnum_retries: 1\r\nper_try_timeout: 0.5s\r\n```\r\n\r\nSeems not related to issue #11369 since HTTP/2 connection is not terminated while this happens.",
